Rosendo Alvarez of Nicaragua retained the WBA junior flyweight title with a majority decision over Colombia's Beibis Mendoza in Little Rock, Arkansas, on Monday. It was their third fight in three years, with Alvarez losing the first before beating Mendoza the second time to take the crown. Judges Russ Perrymore and Oscar Perez judged this 12-rounder 116-112 for Alvarez, while Sonny Ingram scored it a draw at 114. Alvarez took the title from Mendoza on March 3, 2001, and has now given the fighter his only two career losses in 30 fights. Alvarez now lifted his record to 32-2-1 with 21 knockouts. Enditem 